  "id": "wolfssl-rs-epj",
  "title": "wolfhsm API idiomaticity and RustCrypto compatibility",
  "description": "The wolfhsm crate wraps wolfHSM correctly at the FFI level but diverges from RustCrypto conventions in ways that would surprise ecosystem users. This epic tracks findings from the API review: ergonomic shape issues, missing trait implementations, resource-management footguns, type safety gaps, and internal hygiene items. Goal: a crate that feels native to someone already using RustCrypto.",
